The paper deals with the problem of matrix recovery, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel method for matrix recovery that can handle non-linear data structures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with machine learning and computer vision problems. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves optimization and numerical methods.
